value.0: An intimidating magical woman who evidently hails from chult.

Value.value: Ja be careful of da' por'tal der' mh?
Shor' it gets lonely 'ere, bu' I go' meself a way back 'ome der'
Ja bes' be ready fer a fight if ja going in there. *Gestured to the portal*
Eh? Can' ja see I be busy 'ere? *Gestures to her cauldron*

value.0: A foppish-looking explorer. What he's doing settled in this seedy establishment you may never know.

Value.value: Every artist needs the right tool for the job.
I got just what you need.
*Flashes a hand sign on the low.*

value.0: An elder, wispy tiefling. The assortment of scrollcases and wands at his belt suggests him to be the seafaring arcanist-type.

A silky robe it may appear to the normal eye, but as you look closely to the robe's fine cloth, it seems hardened and imbued with small bits of metal.  This may proove useful for defense, and you can certainly feel this has magical properties as well.
This young woman lounges by the shrine with a wry grin ever present on her features.

Arcane Defiance Armors all contain this same inscription:

"Throughout the realms the wielders of magic are advantaged over the common people. We stand in defiance of their tyranny and casual attitudes to power"

Who we are is unknown, but the protection from magic that these items provide is superior.

The cry of the banshee is a nightmare to most. However, to at least one bardic palemaster from Tarkuul it was beauty. He laboured day and night trying to mimic that dreadful keening but every sword was a failure. They could scream, they could howl but none were perfect. Driven mad by his own failure, he cast the wailing swords to the sea and fell into a deep and profound melancholy that lingers to this day.
